    "This approach not only preserves but in some cases enhances the student model's performance, indicating a promising direction for producing resourceefficient LLMs with minimal loss in capabilities.",
    "This section reviews the prevailing research themes related to model compression and knowledge distillation, abstracting from specific models to focus on the broader techniques and their implications.",
    "A. Pruning TechniquesPruning has been widely acknowledged for its effectiveness in reducing the computational complexity of neural networks by eliminating redundant parameters that have minimal impact on the model's performance.",
    "Structured pruning, which removes entire units or layers, can significantly reduce model size while maintaining, and in some cases improving, accuracy [8], [9].",
    "Conversely, unstructured pruning targets individual weights, offering finer granularity at the cost of irregular memory patterns that may not always translate to speedups on conventional hardware [10]."
